
@startuml

' Define classes with their attributes and associations

class City {
  - name: String
  - inhabitants: int
}

class Attraction {
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class GuidedTour {
  - duration: int
  - tourNumber: int
  - maxVisitors: int = 20
}

class Visitor {
  - name: String
}

class Guide {
  - name: String
}

class Discount {
  - amount: float
}

' Relationships

City "1" -- "many" Attraction : has
Attraction "1" -- "many" GuidedTour : offers
GuidedTour "1" -- "1" Guide : requires
GuidedTour "1" -- "many" Visitor : includes
GuidedTour "1" -- "many" Discount : may have
Visitor "1" -- "many" Discount : receives

@enduml

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **City** has multiple **Attractions**.
- Each **Attraction** can offer multiple **GuidedTours**.
- A **GuidedTour** is led by one **Guide**, can include up to 20 **Visitors**, and may have several **Discounts**.
- **Discount** links a **Visitor** to a specific **GuidedTour** with a discount amount.

